  "doc_id": "4346",
  "text": "We used the Differential Expression Analysis for Sequence Count Data (DESeq2 function in R) [CITATION_1] to compare OTU abundance between subject and control groups, controlling the false positive rate at P = 0.05. Parameters extracted for each OTU included log2(fold change), globally adjusted P value and abundance and prevalence information. Two-sided P values are reported throughout.",
